{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "In an increasingly globalized business environment, intercultural competence is essential for effective collaboration, communication, and leadership. This course develops students’ ability to function effectively in multicultural business settings by studying Japanese corporate practices.Grounded in intercultural communication theory, the course examines how cultural values influence organizational behavior, negotiation styles, leadership approaches, corporate strategy,&nbsp;&nbsp;and financial decision-making in Japan. Through case studies of Japanese companies, students will analyze real business situations and evaluate how cultural frameworks shape managerial choices and corporate outcomes.The course emphasizes analytical thinking, reflection, and practical application.&nbsp;", "到達目標": "Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to:1. Explain key theories of intercultural communication and cultural dimensions.2. Identify cultural differences and evaluate their impact on business practices.3. Analyze communication styles and organizational behavior in corporations.4. Apply intercultural frameworks to real corporate case studies to deeper understand the effective collaboration in multicultural business environments.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "Seminar format class. Utilize case studies and critical incidents to provide a deeper understanding of the contents and enhance the ability to apply critical thinking. Work individually or in groups on topics related to the content. Encouraged to reflect on their learning by writing a journal at the end of each class.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">【Startup Week】</span><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Online class（Task-oriented format)</span></div><div><div><span style=\"font-family:-webkit-standard,serif;font-size:10pt;line-height:15.333332px;background-image:none;background-position:0% 0%;background-size:auto;